===Etymology===

/ohoki/: [opoki] > [oɸoki] > [owoki] > [oːki]. A full adjective derived from the older adjectival noun [[大きな|ōkina]]. The adjectival noun ''ōkina'', in turn, derives from the attributive form of cognate [[大し]] "large" or [[多し]] "many", which were not originally distinguished.

